Magma Power Co said it has discontinuedtalks on joint ownership of its new Niland geothermal powerplants in the Imperial Valley of California with SouthernCalifornia Edison Co.    The company said it has retained J.P. Morgan and Co &lt;JPM>to act as financial advisor in arranging equity and debtfinancing for its new geothermal plants in the Imperial Valley.    It said the moves should bring significant financialbenefits to shareholders. Reuter&#3;